  <bioghist id="aspace_88ef6336e83c8b58b05bcd59a03fbbc5">
    <head>Biography</head>
<p>There is very little biographical information available about Mainerd Baker. He was a musician and music copyist in Hollywood from the late 1930s through the early 1980s. Baker worked at many studios and networks and for many arrangers over the years.</p>  </bioghist>
  <scopecontent id="aspace_fd67f349434319735ef91e5c9ac09ff9">
    <head>Scope and Content</head>
<p>The collection consists mostly of radio and television scripts related to the career of musician and music copyist Mainerd Baker. The scripts are from productions in which Baker may have been involved with in some capacity and/or scripts that were given to him by friends from the entertainment business who knew of his interest in collecting scripts. Included are scripts from <title>Gulf Screen Guild Theatre</title>, <title>Inner Sanctum Mysteries</title>, and <title>This is Your Life</title>.</p>  </scopecontent>
  <arrangement id="aspace_6ab1b6e4086cfeb9ab794d0a67438037">
    <head>Organization and Arrangement</head>
<p>The scripts are arranged alphabetically by program title.</p>  </arrangement>
